<meta content='What we can do to die well' itemprop='name'>
<meta content='The healthcare industry in America is so focused on pathology, surgery and pharmacology — on what doctors "do" to patients — that it often overlooks the values of the human beings it&#x0027;s supposed to care for. Palliative care physician Timothy Ihrig explains the benefits of a different approach, one that fosters a patient&#x0027;s overall quality of life and navigates serious illness from diagnosis to death with dignity and compassion.' itemprop='description'>
